<br>
1.  If you sign up, it would make me feel all squishy inside if you were to show.  If too many of the signups are no-shows, or overly late, I will simply call the raid.  I am NOT going to punish the people who show up with an arduous wait, possibly followed by a nasty death and CR.<br>
<br>
2.  Dragon raids take time.  If you cannot deal with that, I am so sorry, this is not the raid for you.  I like to run a tight ship, so I will keep the wait to an absolute minimum.  Patience is a virtue, and if you do not have any, try to fake it when I hum a few bars.<br>
<br>
3.  This is more a personal gripe than rule.  When clearing to the prep are, DO NOT EAT THE PRICKLY PEAR, SHOULD IT DROP.  It is for SKs, and I am sure they would like it.  I *KNOW* my SK would.<br>
<br>
Now to answer the burning question:  Yes, I am a bard, and NO I am not calling the white scale, at least for the first few raids.  I will roll on it like every other Fed bard there.  Eventually, I suppose I will get tired of sitting at level 52, and will call it, so all you other bards be sure to get in on the early raids, lol.  I AM asking that the lucky bard who wins the scale refrain from rolling on any bard instruments that happen to drop.  If you get your scale and want an instrument, come to the next one--we'd love to have you!<br>
<br>
Agurg may have more to add, but I think that's all for me.  (Isn't that enough?)  This can be fun, or this can be like living in a one room house with a dozen silverback gorillas with explosive diarrhea--a stinking, hellish experience*.<br>
<br>
Anson Khaliada<br>
52 Bard of MoS<br>
